    <sec id="s1">
      <title/>
      <p>In <italic>PLoS Biology</italic>, volume 5, issue 4: doi: <ext-link ext-link-type="doi" xlink:href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1371/journal.pbio.0050072" xlink:type="simple">10.1371/journal.pbio.0050072</ext-link></p>
      <p>On page 0801, in the last sentence of the first paragraph of the Results section, “isoleucine” should be replaced with “threonine.”</p>
      <p>The corrected version is:</p>
      <p>“Nonetheless, the overall feature emerging from our analysis is that syntaxins with conserved threonine at the +7 layer appear to be selectively involved in regulated secretion at synapses or neurosecretory cells.”</p>
    </sec>
